name: ASCVDSCT
title: ASCVD SCT
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Definition:This value set intends to capture all SNOMED CT codes that represent atherosclerotic heart disease (CAD), Peripheral Artery Disease (PAD) and Cerebrovascular diseases (CVD) which are also atherosclerotic in origin),(Data Element Scope: CONDITION: CLINICAL_DRIVER:),(Inclusion Criteria: "CAD: Angina- I20*; Acute MI - I21*; Subsequent MI- I22*; Complications Following MI -I23*; Other Acute Ischemic Heart Dz- I24*; Chronic Ischemic Heart Dz- I25*, H/o MI, H/o CABG, H/o stent in place, old MI
CVD: Transient cerebral ischemic attacks and related syndromes- G45*; Vascular syndromes of brain in cerebrovascular diseases-G46*; Cerebral Infarction-I63*; Occlusion and stenosis of precerebral arteries, not resulting in cerebral infarction-I65*; Occlusion and stenosis of cerebral arteries, not resulting in cerebral infarction-I66*;  Cerebral Atherosclerosis-I67.2; Sequelae of Cerebral Infarction-I69.3*
PAD: Atherosclerosis- I70*; "),(Exclusion Criteria: SNOMED SCT codes that are not representative of atherosclerosis: Coronary artery spasm angina-87343002)
